sual evidence of the tragedy of Cambodia's autogenocide. "The most important examination of the subject so far. Without in any way denying the horror and brutality of the Khmers Rouges, the essays adopt a principle of detached analysis which makes their conclusion far more significant and convincing than the superficial images emanating from the television or cinema screen." --Ralph Smith, The Times Literary Supplement "A book that belongs on the shelf of every scholar interested in Cambodia, revolution, or communism. Answers to questions such as `What effect did Khmer society have on the reign of the Khmer Rouge?' focus on understanding, rather than merely describing." --Randall Scott Clemons, Perspectives on Political Science  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 7aHISTORY / Military / Vietnam War.2bisacsh1 aCamey, Tnnothy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarney, Timothy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHawk, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJackson, Karl D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJackson, Karl D., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aPonchaud, François, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aQuinn, Kenneth M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aQuinn, Kenneth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTwining, Charles H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Archive (pre 2000) eBook Packagez978311064968008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press eBook-Package Archive 1927-1999z978311044249640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978140085170